{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels for attendee attribution.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: at least one utterance from a multi-speaker recording is assigned the wrong/missing speaker label in STT output, breaking downstream attribution. This failure depends on real diarization/model output quality, so mocks can hide it (LLM-DEP/COUNTERBALANCE => Agentic floor). Rejected Workflow: behavior text targets STT output preservation itself (\"speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels\"), not a required multi-agentic chain assertion.","test_description":"Run real multi-speaker meeting audio through the production STT API with diarization enabled; assert transcript segments retain correct speaker labels against a labeled fixture and are preserved in the handoff payload used for summarization.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Transcript parsing extracts explicit task assignments (assignee + task text) into summary input structure.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: given a transcript sentence with an explicit assignment, parser output omits either assignee or task text. This is local parsing/structuring logic; no real OS/network/subprocess and no model-quality dependency are required. Rejected Integration+: behavior text is about parsing extraction into an input structure, not cross-service behavior.","test_description":"Feed parser fixture transcripts containing explicit assignments (including edge punctuation/name formats) and assert exact structured extraction fields `{assignee, task_text}` for each assignment.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"L