tive.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: a clearly stated decision in transcript is absent from `decisions` and only present/implicit in narrative output. This depends on real LLM extraction/placement quality; mock outputs would trivially pass and hide the defect. Rejected Workflow: invariant can be tested with one real summarization decision from transcript input; multi-stage agent chaining is not strictly required.","test_description":"Submit transcripts with known decision statements to real summarization, then assert each expected decision is present in structured `decisions` entries and not only narrative text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.18}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"For audio >60 minutes, service segments, processes sequentially, and merges into one coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Minimal failing invariant: segment boundary content is lost/misordered or final merged summary is incoherent across segments despite each segment processing. Validation requires multiple model-involved steps in sequence (segment transcribe/summarize and merge), so MULTI-STEP + AGENTIC floor => Workflow. Integration/System alone can verify orchestration mechanics but can miss coherence and cross-segment semantic failures.","test_description":"Run a real >60-minute recording through production segmentation pipeline; verify sequential segment processing occurred, merged output is structurally complete, and cross-segment decisions/action items remain consistent and non-duplicative in final summary.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"End-to-end pipeline (upload, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output) completes automatically for a real meetin